class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wxx1665702627294.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wxx1665702627294.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wxx1665702627294.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wxx1665702627294\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Unifields\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__unifields_85339\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Unifields are field representations for displaying and entering data in character mode. They also work in Windows, but support only basic video attributes (bright, underline, inverse, and blink). They do not support proportional fonts or other properties.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25406e1_d25407e1_d25408e1\">In character mode, EditBox widgets are automatically\n         mapped to Unifields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25409e1_d25410e1_d25411e1\">In Windows applications, Unifields can be used to improve\n         performance in components with several hundred fields, because they do not require\n         Microsoft Windows resources.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25412e1_d25413e1_d25414e1\">Many GOLD key combinations and text editing functions are\n         recognized only in Unifields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25415e1_d25416e1_d25417e1\">If you use split bars in a component with Unifields, it\n         is possible to edit the Unifields, but layout changes made with the split bars are not\n         applied to the Unifields.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__topic_d17377e1_d17378e1_d17379e1_d17380e1_d17381e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d105085e66\"> Supported Triggers </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25421e1_d25422e1_d25423e1\">Unifields can activate the following triggers:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12572e1_d12573e1_d12574e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqj1665702585000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqj1665702585000.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to an interactive event on a field or entity widget, such as the user clicking on the field.\">trigger detail</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12575e1_d12576e1_d12577e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"viq1665702608478.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/viq1665702608478.html\" title=\"Trigger for reacting to the user's request for online help in a desktop application.\">trigger help</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12578e1_d12579e1_d12580e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wbv1665702600112.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wbv1665702600112.html\" title=\"Trigger that defines what happens after a user successfully leaves a field in a form component.\">trigger loseFocus (Field)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12581e1_d12582e1_d12583e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"duk1665702605725.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/duk1665702605725.html\" title=\"Trigger that handles processing when a user starts to modify a field in a form component.\">trigger startModification</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12584e1_d12585e1_d12586e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kke1665702605570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kke1665702605570.html\" title=\"Interactive trigger for that determines what happens after a user changes the value of a field in a form component.\">trigger valueChanged</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__topic_d17382e1_d17383e1_d17384e1_d17385e1_d17386e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d105085e128\"> ProcScript for Unifields </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25427e1_d25428e1_d25429e1\">The following functions are available only in\n            Unifields.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12587e1_d12588e1_d12589e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"apo1686824392132.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apo1686824392132.html\" title=\"In a Unifield, return the Uniface character code for the key that activated a trigger.\">$char</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12590e1_d12591e1_d12592e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wmy1719769435039.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmy1719769435039.html\" title=\"Return the line on which the cursor is positioned in the current Unifield.\">$curline</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12593e1_d12594e1_d12595e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"grv1719592389957.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/grv1719592389957.html\" title=\"Return the word on which the cursor is positioned in the current Unifield.\">$curword</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__topic_d17387e1_d17388e1_d17389e1_d17390e1_d17391e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d105085e170\"> Configuring Unifields </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25433e1_d25434e1_d25435e1\">The following assignment settings can be used to\n            configure the use of Unifields:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12596e1_d12597e1_d12598e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dvt1665702627513.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dvt1665702627513.html\" title=\"Replace all unifields with edit boxes.\">$NO_UNIFIELDS</a> replaces all Unifields with edit boxes. Use this\n               assignment setting when using languages where characters are primarily read right to\n               left, such as Hebrew or Arabic, or when using language-specific text in ProcScript. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12599e1_d12600e1_d12601e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kig1665702627590.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kig1665702627590.html\" title=\"Set the video attributes for profile characters in unifields.\">$PROFILE_VIDEO</a> sets the video attributes for profile characters\n               that appear in Unifields. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12602e1_d12603e1_d12604e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpv1665702627663.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpv1665702627663.html\" title=\"Specify that the carriage return (CR) character in a multi-line Unifield does not go through the keyboard translation table.\">$UNIFIELD_NO_CR_KTT</a> specifies that the CR character (Enter key) does\n               not go through the keyboard translation table. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__topic_d17392e1_d17393e1_d17394e1_d17395e1_d17396e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d105085e212\"> Video Definitions </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__p_d25439e1_d25440e1_d25441e1\">The following video attributes are available:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12605e1_d12606e1_d12607e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xde1665702627733.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xde1665702627733.html\" title=\"Display Unifields as blinking fields. Use only in a character mode environment.\">Blink</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12608e1_d12609e1_d12610e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"twh1665702627801.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/twh1665702627801.html\" title=\"Display Unifields as bold fields. Use only in a character mode environment.\">Bright</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12611e1_d12612e1_d12613e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wqm1665702627877.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wqm1665702627877.html\" title=\"Display Unifields in inverse highlighting. Use only in a character mode environment.\">Inverse?</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__li_d12614e1_d12615e1_d12616e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dsg1665702627947.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dsg1665702627947.html\" title=\"Display Unifields as underlined fields. Use only in a character mode environment.\">Underline</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"wxx1665702627294__note_w3301ab1b5c17b7_w3302ab1b5c17_w3303ab1b5_w3304ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> In Windows,\n            Unifield video definitions can produce unpredictable results.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Unifields Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Unifields Unifields are field representations for displaying and entering data in character mode. They also work in Windows, but support only basic video attributes (bright, underline, inverse, and blink). They do not support proportional fonts or other properties. In character mode, EditBox widgets are automatically mapped to Unifields. In Windows applications, Unifields can be used to improve performance in components with several hundred fields, because they do not require Microsoft Windows resources. Many GOLD key combinations and text editing functions are recognized only in Unifields. If you use split bars in a component with Unifields, it is possible to edit the Unifields, but layout changes made with the split bars are not applied to the Unifields. Supported Triggers Unifields can activate the following triggers: trigger detail trigger help trigger loseFocus (Field) trigger startModification trigger valueChanged ProcScript for Unifields The following functions are available only in Unifields. $char $curline $curword Configuring Unifields The following assignment settings can be used to configure the use of Unifields: $NO_UNIFIELDS replaces all Unifields with edit boxes. Use this assignment setting when using languages where characters are primarily read right to left, such as Hebrew or Arabic, or when using language-specific text in ProcScript. $PROFILE_VIDEO sets the video attributes for profile characters that appear in Unifields. $UNIFIELD_NO_CR_KTT specifies that the CR character (Enter key) does not go through the keyboard translation table. Video Definitions The following video attributes are available: Blink Bright Inverse? Underline Note: In Windows, Unifield video definitions can produce unpredictable results. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}